1
00:00:10,042 --> 00:00:12,417
-[groans]
-[guard] Come on!

2
00:00:14,708 --> 00:00:16,833
[Dr. Merati]
"They that love beyond the world

3
00:00:16,917 --> 00:00:18,208
cannot be separated by it.

4
00:00:18,542 --> 00:00:20,583
Death cannot kill what never dies."

5
00:00:20,917 --> 00:00:23,792
[Governor] With Vanessa, at least
I had a sense someone had his ear,

6
00:00:23,875 --> 00:00:25,417
someone could rein him in.

7
00:00:25,500 --> 00:00:27,917
Pressure on my office is immense.
I'm getting it from all sides.

8
00:00:28,000 --> 00:00:31,750
Hi, Marge. I am here to solve
your City Hall problem.

9
00:00:32,208 --> 00:00:34,167
[Buck] We work for a man
who can change your life.

10
00:00:34,250 --> 00:00:37,458
All he asks in return is loyalty.
Make a choice.

11
00:00:37,958 --> 00:00:39,542
-What is this?
-Daniel, please.

12
00:00:39,625 --> 00:00:41,417
I don't even know
if I can protect you anymore.

13
00:00:41,500 --> 00:00:42,625
Protect me from what?

14
00:00:42,708 --> 00:00:44,417
-[cell phone buzzes]
-From him.

15
00:00:46,208 --> 00:00:49,333
[Fisk] We have reason to believe
that Matt Murdock survived the attack.

16
00:00:49,417 --> 00:00:51,417
Help find the lawyer from Hell's Kitchen.

17
00:00:51,500 --> 00:00:53,667
Let's bring this hero home.

18
00:00:53,750 --> 00:00:54,792
Thank you.

19
00:00:55,667 --> 00:00:57,833
-[groans]
-I can't let you do it, Karen.

20
00:00:57,917 --> 00:01:01,375
[Karen] What if this doesn't end
until one of you goes down?

21
00:01:01,458 --> 00:01:03,333
Push those motherfuckers back!

22
00:01:05,458 --> 00:01:06,625
Holy shit.

23
00:01:06,708 --> 00:01:08,875
Karen fuckin' Page.

24
00:01:18,208 --> 00:01:21,917
[sirens wailing in distance]

25
00:01:25,583 --> 00:01:26,583
[man] One avocado.

26
00:01:29,167 --> 00:01:31,208
[reporter 1] According to
city officials, vigilantes...

27
00:01:31,292 --> 00:01:32,583
[reporter 2]
...riots at City Hall...

28
00:01:32,667 --> 00:01:35,708
[reporter 3] Last night's attack
on City Hall by criminals...

29
00:01:36,542 --> 00:01:39,542
-[man yells indistinctly]
-[sirens wail, helicopter hovers]

30
00:01:39,625 --> 00:01:42,167
-[reporter 4] Protesters...
-[reporter 5] ...attacked by Task Force.

31
00:01:44,875 --> 00:01:46,917
-Three injured.
-[reporter 4] Two dead.

32
00:01:48,333 --> 00:01:51,833
[reporter 6] Mayor Fisk vows
to restore order to this city.

33
00:01:53,042 --> 00:01:56,375
[♪ psychedelic rock music playing,
David Bowie "It Ain't Easy"]

34
00:01:56,458 --> 00:02:00,333
♪ When you climb
to the top of the mountain ♪

35
00:02:00,458 --> 00:02:03,667
♪ Look out over the sea ♪

36
00:02:04,458 --> 00:02:10,625
♪ Think about the places, perhaps
where a young man could be ♪

37
00:02:10,708 --> 00:02:15,167
♪ Then you jump back down
to the rooftops ♪

38
00:02:15,250 --> 00:02:18,375
♪ Look out over the town ♪

39
00:02:18,458 --> 00:02:22,042
♪ Think about all of the strange things ♪

40
00:02:22,125 --> 00:02:24,292
♪ Circulating 'round ♪

41
00:02:24,375 --> 00:02:27,792
♪ It ain't easy ♪

42
00:02:27,875 --> 00:02:30,292
♪ It ain't easy ♪

43
00:02:31,333 --> 00:02:36,542
♪ It ain't easy to get to heaven
when you're goin' down ♪

44
00:02:38,833 --> 00:02:43,500
♪ Well, all the people
have got their problems ♪

45
00:02:43,583 --> 00:02:45,708
♪ That ain't nothin' new ♪

46
00:02:47,125 --> 00:02:50,750
♪ With the help of the good Lord ♪

47
00:02:50,833 --> 00:02:53,417
♪ We can all pull on through ♪

48
00:02:53,500 --> 00:02:55,875
♪ We can all pull on through ♪

49
00:02:55,958 --> 00:02:57,500
[inmates chattering indistinctly]

50
00:02:57,583 --> 00:03:00,958
♪ And get there in the end ♪

51
00:03:01,042 --> 00:03:04,375
♪ Sometimes it'll take you right up ♪

52
00:03:04,458 --> 00:03:07,083
♪ And sometimes down again ♪

53
00:03:07,167 --> 00:03:10,667
♪ It ain't easy ♪

54
00:03:10,750 --> 00:03:14,042
♪ It ain't easy ♪

55
00:03:14,125 --> 00:03:19,167
♪ It ain't easy to get to heaven
when you're goin' down ♪

56
00:03:19,250 --> 00:03:23,708
-[door buzzes open, closes]
-♪ It ain't easy ♪

57
00:03:23,792 --> 00:03:25,958
[woman] I don't know.
Come on, everybody.

58
00:03:26,042 --> 00:03:27,625
Hey, where are my cigarettes?

59
00:03:27,708 --> 00:03:32,458
♪ It ain't easy to get to heaven
when you're goin' down ♪

60
00:03:52,167 --> 00:03:53,625
[Fisk] Hello, Miss Page.

61
00:03:55,875 --> 00:03:58,792
You have... taken people from me.

62
00:04:01,458 --> 00:04:03,750
And out there, they believe that you're...

63
00:04:04,208 --> 00:04:05,542
a hero.

64
00:04:06,417 --> 00:04:08,125
Yet I believe in order.

65
00:04:09,833 --> 00:04:11,125
And you are a criminal.

66
00:04:11,875 --> 00:04:12,875
Worse,

67
00:04:13,167 --> 00:04:15,875
you're the sidekick
of a deranged vigilante.

68
00:04:17,750 --> 00:04:18,750
You,

69
00:04:19,042 --> 00:04:21,000
broken and deluded,

70
00:04:21,667 --> 00:04:23,500
you abet his crimes.

71
00:04:24,167 --> 00:04:25,167
For what?

72
00:04:26,083 --> 00:04:27,208
Love?

73
00:04:28,458 --> 00:04:29,792
Ha!

74
00:04:48,000 --> 00:04:50,167
You know,
I've never seen you scared before.

75
00:04:52,292 --> 00:04:53,500
I kinda like it.

76
00:04:54,583 --> 00:04:56,792
No, not fear.

77
00:04:56,875 --> 00:04:58,667
[gasps, winces]

78
00:04:59,167 --> 00:05:00,500
-[choking]
-Order,

79
00:05:00,583 --> 00:05:01,583
Miss Page.

80
00:05:02,292 --> 00:05:03,292
Order.

81
00:05:03,542 --> 00:05:04,792
No, no.

82
00:05:04,875 --> 00:05:07,542
No, you took it too far last night,
and you know it.

83
00:05:07,625 --> 00:05:09,500
And the city knows it!

84
00:05:09,583 --> 00:05:11,875
[choking]

85
00:05:12,833 --> 00:05:15,750
[gasps and coughs]

86
00:05:16,708 --> 00:05:18,542
You have one phone call.

87
00:05:19,917 --> 00:05:21,333
Choose it wisely.

88
00:05:21,417 --> 00:05:23,708
[pants, chuckles softly]

89
00:05:29,250 --> 00:05:32,542
[♪ theme music playing]

90
00:07:10,792 --> 00:07:13,333
[snoring]

91
00:07:15,167 --> 00:07:17,375
-[gasps]
-Good morning, sunshine.

92
00:07:17,458 --> 00:07:18,708
Jessica.

93
00:07:18,792 --> 00:07:20,250
Wait. Hold, hold, hold on.

94
00:07:20,333 --> 00:07:22,000
Listen, before you choose violence--

95
00:07:22,083 --> 00:07:23,958
You sent your assholes to my house.

96
00:07:24,042 --> 00:07:26,458
That was a mistake. They were
just supposed to tell you to back off.

97
00:07:26,542 --> 00:07:27,792
With my daughter there.

98
00:07:27,875 --> 00:07:30,083
I would never hurt your kid--
I love children.

99
00:07:30,167 --> 00:07:31,292
You listen to me.

100
00:07:31,375 --> 00:07:34,542
If you ever come at me
or Danielle ever again,

101
00:07:34,625 --> 00:07:36,375
-I swear to God, I will kill you.
-[groans]

102
00:07:36,875 --> 00:07:38,333
-Do you understand me?
-Yeah.

103
00:07:38,417 --> 00:07:39,500
Please don't kill me.

104
00:07:40,458 --> 00:07:42,875
Also, I'm not really sure you can anymore,

105
00:07:42,958 --> 00:07:46,083
'cause a little birdie said your powers
ain't what they used to be.

106
00:07:49,458 --> 00:07:51,250
Speaking of little birdies,

107
00:07:51,917 --> 00:07:53,167
you're talkin' a lotta shit

108
00:07:53,250 --> 00:07:56,250
for a guy sittin' there in his underwear
with very limited options.

109
00:07:56,333 --> 00:07:59,750
Don't forget, I am the only one
that can connect you

110
00:08:00,167 --> 00:08:01,167
with Luke.

111
00:08:05,792 --> 00:08:06,958
Where is he?

112
00:08:07,042 --> 00:08:09,250
He is overseas.
He's doin' the Lord's work,

113
00:08:09,333 --> 00:08:10,333
so you don't have to.

114
00:08:10,792 --> 00:08:14,208
-You're behind Fisk's arms deal.
-No, I'm not.

115
00:08:14,292 --> 00:08:16,917
Because a couple
anti-social vigilantes blew 'em up.

116
00:08:17,000 --> 00:08:18,917
No arms, no deal. [scoffs]

117
00:08:19,000 --> 00:08:21,500
-Thanks for that, by the way.
-Why are you covering for him?

118
00:08:21,583 --> 00:08:22,667
I'm not, not anymore.

119
00:08:23,208 --> 00:08:24,500
It's actually the opposite.

120
00:08:26,208 --> 00:08:27,792
The Governor wants Fisk...

121
00:08:28,417 --> 00:08:30,083
-out.
-Good, that's...

122
00:08:30,167 --> 00:08:31,208
That's great news.

123
00:08:31,292 --> 00:08:34,208
Yeah, except he just went apeshit
on his own voters.

124
00:08:34,292 --> 00:08:35,708
I don't think she can do it.

125
00:08:36,417 --> 00:08:39,333
The way I see it,
this goes all kinds of wrong

126
00:08:39,667 --> 00:08:41,250
for Governor McCaffrey.

127
00:08:42,958 --> 00:08:46,833
[scoffs] Oh, Christ.

128
00:08:47,958 --> 00:08:49,625
[Matt] Fisk is gonna kill the Governor?

129
00:08:50,083 --> 00:08:51,750
[Jess] That's what Charles suggested.

130
00:08:52,042 --> 00:08:53,292
Very strongly.

131
00:08:53,375 --> 00:08:54,375
And you believe him?

132
00:08:55,000 --> 00:08:57,500
This guy was working with Fisk
until about a minute ago.

133
00:08:58,167 --> 00:09:01,000
I don't believe a word that asshole says,
but in this case...

134
00:09:01,083 --> 00:09:02,750
-Yeah.
-...it does track.

135
00:09:03,833 --> 00:09:07,583
[sighs] She's the only one
who can revoke the Freeport's charter.

136
00:09:08,708 --> 00:09:11,708
If Fisk puts one of his puppets
in the Governor's office,

137
00:09:12,708 --> 00:09:13,708
New York is his.

138
00:09:14,292 --> 00:09:16,333
And we are on another rooftop.

139
00:09:16,667 --> 00:09:19,417
Yeah, I'm meeting a friend.
Cherry, Jessica. Jessica, Cherry.

140
00:09:19,500 --> 00:09:21,208
Hey, big fan of your work.

141
00:09:21,750 --> 00:09:22,750
Go on.

142
00:09:23,208 --> 00:09:24,208
And?

143
00:09:25,375 --> 00:09:27,625
-Karen's at the 15th Precinct.
-Nice, thank you, Cherry.

144
00:09:27,708 --> 00:09:29,292
All right, now, hold on there, cowboy.

145
00:09:29,375 --> 00:09:30,792
They booked her legit.

146
00:09:30,875 --> 00:09:33,042
Prints, photo, phone call, the works.

147
00:09:33,542 --> 00:09:35,542
They're fast-trackin' her
to Vigilante Court.

148
00:09:35,625 --> 00:09:38,542
You go in there and bust her out,
you are the criminal he says you are.

149
00:09:38,625 --> 00:09:39,875
She's not safe there.

150
00:09:39,958 --> 00:09:42,167
If he was gonna hurt her,
he'd have done it already.

151
00:09:42,250 --> 00:09:45,750
Look, I'm told he went to the precinct,
they talked, he left.

152
00:09:47,125 --> 00:09:48,167
Fisk?

153
00:09:48,708 --> 00:09:49,875
Son of a bitch.

154
00:09:51,292 --> 00:09:52,417
He's making it legal.

155
00:09:54,125 --> 00:09:55,542
We have anybody at the 15th?

156
00:09:55,625 --> 00:09:57,792
We do. Come on, Matt, I'm all over this.

157
00:09:59,958 --> 00:10:02,083
And you? You stickin' around?

158
00:10:04,208 --> 00:10:05,625
I haven't decided yet.

159
00:10:05,708 --> 00:10:06,792
City needs you.

160
00:10:06,875 --> 00:10:09,042
Tsk. I've heard that before.

161
00:10:09,125 --> 00:10:10,542
[chuckles] Me, too.

162
00:10:11,292 --> 00:10:12,958
-Nice to meet you, Cherry.
-You, too.

163
00:10:13,583 --> 00:10:14,583
Matt.

164
00:10:16,042 --> 00:10:18,042
So, what do ya think?
Are you gonna hit the 15th?

165
00:10:18,125 --> 00:10:20,000
I don't know. There might be another way.

166
00:10:20,083 --> 00:10:21,583
-We--
-I can't help you there.

167
00:10:22,167 --> 00:10:23,875
I did what I came here to do.

168
00:10:23,958 --> 00:10:25,625
I got Charles off my ass.

169
00:10:26,875 --> 00:10:28,542
I need to get home. I have Danielle.

170
00:10:28,625 --> 00:10:31,333
I know, you don't need to explain.
I understand.

171
00:10:31,417 --> 00:10:32,833
Fisk isn't gonna stop.

172
00:10:34,500 --> 00:10:36,167
Unless someone puts him down.

173
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:38,125
Forgotten how encouraging you were.

174
00:10:39,500 --> 00:10:40,708
Don't get yourself killed.

175
00:10:43,083 --> 00:10:44,250
The city needs you.

176
00:10:57,083 --> 00:10:58,875
[bones cracking]

177
00:11:15,208 --> 00:11:16,208
So...

178
00:11:18,000 --> 00:11:19,000
what now?

179
00:11:20,417 --> 00:11:21,875
You wanted one good deed, right?

180
00:11:23,125 --> 00:11:24,667
So we could balance the scales?

181
00:11:25,167 --> 00:11:26,208
-Yeah.
-All right.

182
00:11:26,292 --> 00:11:27,875
-Sure.
-I got it for you.

183
00:11:30,208 --> 00:11:31,583
But first, know this.

184
00:11:34,167 --> 00:11:35,625
I hate you for Foggy.

185
00:11:38,125 --> 00:11:39,500
I hate you for Father Lantom,

186
00:11:39,583 --> 00:11:40,833
for Agent Nadeem.

187
00:11:42,625 --> 00:11:46,083
And every life you've wasted for no reason
other than your own twisted soul.

188
00:11:48,458 --> 00:11:49,917
Part of me wants to kill you.

189
00:11:52,625 --> 00:11:53,625
And...

190
00:11:55,417 --> 00:11:57,083
part of me needs to forgive you.

191
00:11:58,458 --> 00:11:59,458
Yeah.

192
00:12:01,708 --> 00:12:03,375
Well... [clears throat]

193
00:12:06,250 --> 00:12:07,250
Thanks.

194
00:12:07,958 --> 00:12:08,958
Don't do that.

195
00:12:09,042 --> 00:12:10,792
It's not for you, it's for them.

196
00:12:11,792 --> 00:12:13,125
Now go, disappear,

197
00:12:13,208 --> 00:12:14,417
die, I don't care.

198
00:12:15,875 --> 00:12:17,292
But if you mean what you say,

199
00:12:18,750 --> 00:12:21,042
you wanna do one good thing
in a life full of shit,

200
00:12:21,667 --> 00:12:22,750
I got it for ya.

201
00:12:24,500 --> 00:12:27,083
You know I can't make any promises, right?

202
00:12:31,083 --> 00:12:32,542
Wouldn't believe you if you did.

203
00:12:40,667 --> 00:12:42,250
What do you want me to do?

204
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:45,667
[♪ suspenseful music playing]

205
00:12:48,917 --> 00:12:50,792
[police sirens wailing]

206
00:12:55,167 --> 00:12:56,750
[footsteps approaching]

207
00:13:06,083 --> 00:13:07,083
Brett.

208
00:13:08,000 --> 00:13:09,750
-Hey.
-Hey, Karen.

209
00:13:11,042 --> 00:13:12,042
It's been a while.

210
00:13:12,125 --> 00:13:13,125
Yeah.

211
00:13:14,000 --> 00:13:16,333
[sighs] Wondered why
they brought me to the 15th.

212
00:13:16,417 --> 00:13:19,083
Hey, you know, Chief of Detective
gets to pull a few strings.

213
00:13:19,167 --> 00:13:21,042
Yeah, yeah. Hotshot, huh?

214
00:13:24,500 --> 00:13:25,500
Fisk was here.

215
00:13:26,833 --> 00:13:27,833
I know.

216
00:13:28,458 --> 00:13:29,750
Only so much I can do.

217
00:13:30,833 --> 00:13:31,833
I know.

218
00:13:36,083 --> 00:13:37,417
-What are you doing?
-[unlocking]

219
00:13:38,417 --> 00:13:39,417
Come with me.

220
00:13:41,083 --> 00:13:42,083
Come.

221
00:13:46,917 --> 00:13:48,083
Let's go.

222
00:13:59,125 --> 00:14:00,667
[Daredevil sighs in relief]

223
00:14:04,833 --> 00:14:06,500
-I'm so sorry.
-I'm sorry.

224
00:14:06,917 --> 00:14:08,875
I'm sorry,
I shouldn't have said what I did.

225
00:14:08,958 --> 00:14:09,958
You know...

226
00:14:11,083 --> 00:14:13,375
we all gotta stop meeting up like this.

227
00:14:14,167 --> 00:14:15,792
I can't cover for that long, but...

228
00:14:16,458 --> 00:14:17,542
you got one minute.

229
00:14:17,625 --> 00:14:18,625
-Okay.
-Thank you.

230
00:14:18,708 --> 00:14:19,833
Listen, we don't
have much time,

231
00:14:19,917 --> 00:14:21,417
-I need--
-I can't go with you.

232
00:14:21,792 --> 00:14:23,667
No, I know. I didn't come to get you.

233
00:14:24,042 --> 00:14:25,458
Fucking great minds, huh?

234
00:14:27,375 --> 00:14:30,542
Look, I don't know what this is, but
it feels like an opportunity. I think...

235
00:14:30,625 --> 00:14:32,708
I have to stay.
I have to face him in court.

236
00:14:36,250 --> 00:14:37,792
They tell you he came to see me?

237
00:14:38,542 --> 00:14:40,667
-You okay?
-[sighs] I'm alive.

238
00:14:41,875 --> 00:14:42,917
He's different.

239
00:14:44,042 --> 00:14:45,500
I don't know
what's going on in his mind,

240
00:14:45,583 --> 00:14:48,208
but he's scheming, and he's planning,
and he's way the hell ahead of us.

241
00:14:48,292 --> 00:14:49,625
I just don't think we can run.

242
00:14:49,708 --> 00:14:50,708
Yeah.

243
00:14:51,292 --> 00:14:53,250
'Cause he's losing the city
and he knows it.

244
00:14:54,333 --> 00:14:57,792
So, he's gonna prosecute you
and humiliate you.

245
00:14:59,042 --> 00:15:00,250
Publicly, legitimately,

246
00:15:00,958 --> 00:15:02,542
and make everyone cheer for it.

247
00:15:06,917 --> 00:15:08,208
Can't say it's not smart.

248
00:15:11,875 --> 00:15:13,792
-That means there'll be cameras.
-Mmm-hmm.

249
00:15:15,125 --> 00:15:16,750
-Exactly.
-Holy shit.

250
00:15:17,917 --> 00:15:18,917
Turns out,

251
00:15:19,333 --> 00:15:21,792
we may have to cross lines
to stop him. Just...

252
00:15:22,625 --> 00:15:23,875
not the ones you think.

253
00:15:25,708 --> 00:15:26,708
Well, then...

254
00:15:33,000 --> 00:15:34,333
No. No.

255
00:15:35,083 --> 00:15:36,083
Matt, you can't.

256
00:15:37,750 --> 00:15:38,875
Yes, I can.

257
00:15:41,458 --> 00:15:43,208
[Brett] All right, time's up.
Let's go.

258
00:15:57,250 --> 00:15:59,417
-I'll be there when you need me.
-[sniffles]

259
00:16:00,125 --> 00:16:01,125
Better be.

260
00:16:17,708 --> 00:16:19,167
[Hochberg] Aiding and abetting murder,

261
00:16:19,250 --> 00:16:22,375
providing material support
to known terrorist, Daredevil.

262
00:16:22,458 --> 00:16:25,375
And that's to say
nothing of inciting a riot.

263
00:16:25,708 --> 00:16:27,750
Just a matter of picking
our strongest charges.

264
00:16:27,833 --> 00:16:29,417
Charge her on all of them.

265
00:16:29,750 --> 00:16:31,083
Convict her on all of them.

266
00:16:32,042 --> 00:16:34,625
-Well, sir, given the time crunch--
-All of them.

267
00:16:36,375 --> 00:16:37,375
Right.

268
00:16:37,917 --> 00:16:38,917
Sir.

269
00:16:39,417 --> 00:16:42,250
Do you know the AG
is gonna want to be involved?

270
00:16:43,792 --> 00:16:45,167
Oh, uh...

271
00:16:46,750 --> 00:16:48,583
Well, what he and Albany wants

272
00:16:48,667 --> 00:16:50,333
is irrelevant at this point.

273
00:16:51,958 --> 00:16:52,958
[knocking on door]

274
00:16:55,750 --> 00:16:58,375
-Dr. Glenn.
-Sir, you asked to see me?

275
00:16:58,458 --> 00:16:59,875
[Fisk] Yes, please come in.

276
00:17:00,375 --> 00:17:02,708
Mr. Hochberg and I,
we were finished, weren't we?

277
00:17:03,417 --> 00:17:05,250
Uh... Of course.

278
00:17:06,792 --> 00:17:07,792
Dr. Glenn,

279
00:17:08,583 --> 00:17:09,917
it's always such a pleasure.

280
00:17:10,000 --> 00:17:11,000
I...

281
00:17:11,083 --> 00:17:14,958
might need a little of your expertise
on this trial, if I may.

282
00:17:15,792 --> 00:17:16,792
Of course.

283
00:17:21,083 --> 00:17:24,250
District Attorney Hochberg is
an interesting fellow, isn't he?

284
00:17:25,875 --> 00:17:28,000
He's a very skilled litigator.

285
00:17:28,083 --> 00:17:29,625
He makes my skin crawl.

286
00:17:30,125 --> 00:17:31,125
[chuckles softly]

287
00:17:31,750 --> 00:17:33,250
Lawyers, you know, they...

288
00:17:34,500 --> 00:17:37,417
use words to twist the truth, don't they?

289
00:17:39,542 --> 00:17:41,167
I think I know what you mean.

290
00:17:41,458 --> 00:17:42,542
I imagine you do.

291
00:17:44,833 --> 00:17:46,292
I wanted to check on you...

292
00:17:47,625 --> 00:17:48,917
person-to-person.

293
00:17:50,625 --> 00:17:51,750
How are you, sir?

294
00:17:53,333 --> 00:17:54,750
I... I don't know.

295
00:17:56,125 --> 00:17:57,750
I haven't been asked that.

296
00:18:06,250 --> 00:18:07,292
I always...

297
00:18:10,125 --> 00:18:12,500
accepted love as a prison.

298
00:18:16,833 --> 00:18:19,375
I just never expected

299
00:18:19,458 --> 00:18:21,292
to be in it alone.

300
00:18:22,417 --> 00:18:24,208
[Heather] Condolences are meaningless.

301
00:18:24,667 --> 00:18:26,375
Thoughts and prayers do nothing.

302
00:18:27,417 --> 00:18:30,000
No one tells you the truth
in times like this,

303
00:18:30,083 --> 00:18:31,083
which is...

304
00:18:32,042 --> 00:18:33,208
This is gonna hurt.

305
00:18:34,792 --> 00:18:35,792
And...

306
00:18:36,375 --> 00:18:37,417
we don't know when,

307
00:18:38,042 --> 00:18:39,458
or if it's going to end.

308
00:18:41,167 --> 00:18:42,167
No.

309
00:18:43,833 --> 00:18:44,833
Well, I...

310
00:18:45,708 --> 00:18:46,708
I, uh...

311
00:18:48,458 --> 00:18:50,292
I appreciate your words.

312
00:19:06,750 --> 00:19:08,958
Mayor Fisk, I am so sorry,

313
00:19:09,042 --> 00:19:10,875
-I was--
-You don't have to apologize.

314
00:19:11,917 --> 00:19:13,458
It's curious, isn't it?

315
00:19:13,792 --> 00:19:15,500
When we act on impulse...

316
00:19:18,125 --> 00:19:20,167
we surprise even ourselves.

317
00:19:20,250 --> 00:19:21,792
I'd like to think I have

318
00:19:22,375 --> 00:19:23,833
more self-control than that.

319
00:19:23,917 --> 00:19:25,125
But you didn't.

320
00:19:27,125 --> 00:19:29,958
No. [chuckles softly]

321
00:19:35,083 --> 00:19:37,917
-[♪ suspenseful music playing]
-[sirens wailing]

322
00:19:43,500 --> 00:19:46,667
-[camera shutters clicking]
-[crowd clamoring indistinctly]

323
00:19:55,958 --> 00:19:58,500
[clamoring continues]

324
00:20:20,917 --> 00:20:22,583
-[BB] Can I get my shit back?
-No.

325
00:20:24,208 --> 00:20:26,125
This is kidnapping, you know.

326
00:20:27,792 --> 00:20:29,750
Okay, look, I understand that you're mad,

327
00:20:29,833 --> 00:20:31,458
-but--
-No, I'm not mad.

328
00:20:31,542 --> 00:20:32,750
I'm more than mad.

329
00:20:32,833 --> 00:20:34,458
Mad doesn't even begin to cover it.

330
00:20:35,875 --> 00:20:38,000
I can't keep stalling Buck.

331
00:20:38,083 --> 00:20:39,333
Dude, fuck him!

332
00:20:39,417 --> 00:20:40,708
Fuck him? Fuck you!

333
00:20:41,292 --> 00:20:43,667
Look, I get it, you used me, I used you.

334
00:20:43,750 --> 00:20:46,583
But I'm sorry, I thought
we actually had each other's backs.

335
00:20:47,625 --> 00:20:49,375
Your City Without Fear bullshit?

336
00:20:49,875 --> 00:20:51,000
It fucked us.

337
00:20:51,083 --> 00:20:53,583
So, what, you were working
with Karen Page?

338
00:20:58,125 --> 00:20:59,125
Wow.

339
00:20:59,583 --> 00:21:01,375
-How could you?
-How could I?

340
00:21:01,458 --> 00:21:04,042
I started The BB Report in my dorm room.

341
00:21:04,125 --> 00:21:07,250
I put every dime
and every hour of my life into it.

342
00:21:07,625 --> 00:21:10,208
Okay, people trusted it. It was real.

343
00:21:10,583 --> 00:21:14,625
And you turned it into some plastic
commercial for Fisk's fascist New York.

344
00:21:14,708 --> 00:21:17,333
-I didn't see you complaining.
-Okay. Well, clearly,

345
00:21:17,417 --> 00:21:20,708
you didn't see City Without Fear.
That's complaining.

346
00:21:21,458 --> 00:21:23,750
And all for what?
So that you can get outta Staten

347
00:21:23,833 --> 00:21:25,917
-and get a douchebag condo?
-Stop!

348
00:21:27,208 --> 00:21:28,458
He killed my uncle.

349
00:21:28,542 --> 00:21:29,833
-You don't know that.
-Yes,

350
00:21:30,458 --> 00:21:32,417
I do. And you do, too.

351
00:21:33,125 --> 00:21:35,792
You've just decided to turn a blind eye,
and that is your problem.

352
00:21:35,875 --> 00:21:36,958
Fine.

353
00:21:37,042 --> 00:21:38,625
Whatever. I did.

354
00:21:39,000 --> 00:21:41,208
It is, but you don't understand.

355
00:21:41,292 --> 00:21:42,792
That doesn't matter anymore.

356
00:21:43,250 --> 00:21:47,708
Because right now, Buck Cashman
is waiting for me to hand you over to him.

357
00:21:48,833 --> 00:21:50,042
And if I don't,

358
00:21:50,667 --> 00:21:51,875
then he comes after me.

359
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,083
And then you,

360
00:21:54,583 --> 00:21:55,583
and my mom,

361
00:21:56,250 --> 00:21:57,750
and anyone I care about.

362
00:21:58,125 --> 00:22:01,208
So, BB, you should be fucking terrified
right now, 'cause I am.

363
00:22:01,875 --> 00:22:02,875
Then...

364
00:22:03,458 --> 00:22:05,125
we should probably get out of here.

365
00:22:06,083 --> 00:22:07,458
Yeah, we probably should.

366
00:22:10,333 --> 00:22:12,000
-Give me my phone.
-No.

367
00:22:12,083 --> 00:22:14,417
-Why?
-Because I don't trust you.

368
00:22:15,625 --> 00:22:17,292
Just give me a second to fucking think.

369
00:22:17,375 --> 00:22:19,250
Just sit there and let me think.

370
00:22:19,750 --> 00:22:21,792
[scoffs] Okay.

371
00:22:25,625 --> 00:22:26,625
We need a safe house.

372
00:22:26,708 --> 00:22:28,417
What are you, Jason Bourne?

373
00:22:28,500 --> 00:22:29,583
No, just...

374
00:22:31,042 --> 00:22:33,417
Some place Buck doesn't know about.

375
00:22:37,125 --> 00:22:39,125
I have a friend. A finance buddy.

376
00:22:39,208 --> 00:22:41,167
Works mostly in Hong Kong. I'll text him.

377
00:22:41,625 --> 00:22:42,792
Great.

378
00:22:44,750 --> 00:22:45,750
[sighs]

379
00:22:49,458 --> 00:22:50,667
[vibrates]

380
00:22:50,750 --> 00:22:53,208
[reporter] ...Assistant District Attorney
Kirsten McDuffie...

381
00:22:53,292 --> 00:22:55,792
Daniel is proving to be
quite a team player.

382
00:22:56,375 --> 00:22:57,375
Yes, he is.

383
00:22:57,792 --> 00:23:00,292
It's not easy to make the hard decisions.

384
00:23:01,750 --> 00:23:03,708
You think Karen Page knows?

385
00:23:04,042 --> 00:23:05,208
[Buck] Knows what, sir?

386
00:23:05,667 --> 00:23:07,792
That she is the wounded soldier

387
00:23:08,292 --> 00:23:10,167
screaming in the field,

388
00:23:10,583 --> 00:23:13,500
drawing her comrades
into the line of fire.

389
00:23:17,375 --> 00:23:19,833
-[people chattering indistinctly]
-[woman] Really?

390
00:23:20,208 --> 00:23:21,667
-That's good.
-Either way...

391
00:23:36,042 --> 00:23:37,500
[court officer] All rise.

392
00:23:45,333 --> 00:23:47,125
[Chief Justice Waters]
District Attorney Hochberg,

393
00:23:47,208 --> 00:23:48,750
your opening statement.

394
00:23:51,958 --> 00:23:52,958
Your Honors...

395
00:23:56,125 --> 00:23:59,375
I stand before you today
to ask that you convict

396
00:24:00,625 --> 00:24:02,292
and that you punish this woman,

397
00:24:03,083 --> 00:24:05,583
this criminal, Karen Page,

398
00:24:06,333 --> 00:24:09,250
for the crime she has committed
against our great city.

399
00:24:09,333 --> 00:24:11,875
Your Honors, I could argue
my client's innocence.

400
00:24:12,625 --> 00:24:15,750
I could argue
the illegitimacy of this court.

401
00:24:16,708 --> 00:24:18,583
I could argue against

402
00:24:19,000 --> 00:24:20,333
the Safer Streets Act.

403
00:24:20,417 --> 00:24:24,417
But first, I want you to think on
one very important concept.

404
00:24:26,000 --> 00:24:27,417
What is a vigilante?

405
00:24:28,333 --> 00:24:31,083
Is it he or she who breaks the law

406
00:24:31,167 --> 00:24:35,125
in order to get
their own version of justice? Or...

407
00:24:35,500 --> 00:24:37,583
is a vigilante the last resort

408
00:24:37,667 --> 00:24:39,167
to obtain the justice

409
00:24:39,250 --> 00:24:41,917
that a broken society
can no longer supply?

410
00:24:42,000 --> 00:24:44,333
The evidence will show that

411
00:24:45,042 --> 00:24:47,000
Miss Page is not a hero.

412
00:24:48,000 --> 00:24:49,583
She's not a "freedom fighter"

413
00:24:49,667 --> 00:24:51,708
for a noble resistance. No.

414
00:24:51,792 --> 00:24:52,792
No, she's...

415
00:24:53,292 --> 00:24:54,375
a criminal

416
00:24:55,167 --> 00:24:58,625
responsible for the destruction
of innocent human lives.

417
00:24:59,167 --> 00:25:02,292
[Kirsten] Your Honors,
you have a duty to this city,

418
00:25:02,375 --> 00:25:05,458
and you have a duty
to the ideals of this court,

419
00:25:07,125 --> 00:25:11,250
and fulfilling that duty
can only come to one conclusion.

420
00:25:11,333 --> 00:25:12,333
Guilty.

421
00:25:12,417 --> 00:25:13,583
Not guilty.

422
00:25:15,833 --> 00:25:16,833
Thank you.

423
00:25:17,667 --> 00:25:19,708
Prosecution can now call
its first witness.

424
00:25:19,792 --> 00:25:21,750
Your Honors, before we proceed...

425
00:25:22,625 --> 00:25:24,333
I'd like to bring in my co-counsel.

426
00:25:24,417 --> 00:25:26,250
[Hochberg] What-- Co-counsel?

427
00:25:26,333 --> 00:25:28,375
What, already calling for backup?

428
00:25:32,125 --> 00:25:33,792
[audience gasps]

429
00:25:34,208 --> 00:25:36,250
Matthew Murdock
for the defense, Your Honors.

430
00:25:37,042 --> 00:25:38,875
-[woman 1] Oh, my God!
-[man] Is that Matt Murdock?

431
00:25:38,958 --> 00:25:41,208
-[woman 2] Matt Murdock?
-[woman 3] My God. It's Matt Murdock?

432
00:25:41,292 --> 00:25:42,833
[Chief Justice Waters] Order in the court.

433
00:25:42,917 --> 00:25:44,625
[reporter] In a shocking turn of events,

434
00:25:44,708 --> 00:25:47,292
Matthew Murdock,
the missing lawyer from Hell's Kitchen,

435
00:25:47,375 --> 00:25:49,375
has just walked into the courtroom.

436
00:25:49,458 --> 00:25:51,958
Despite a citywide search,
Murdock has not been seen

437
00:25:52,042 --> 00:25:54,917
since the destruction of
his Brooklyn apartment months ago.

438
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:58,208
Murdock is well known for
his heroic act of saving Mayor Fisk

439
00:25:58,292 --> 00:25:59,792
from vigilante gunfire.

440
00:25:59,875 --> 00:26:02,458
But he has now reappeared,
apparently, to support...

441
00:26:08,167 --> 00:26:09,292
[Matt] Officer Powell,

442
00:26:09,375 --> 00:26:13,083
tell me, what is the mission statement
for the Anti-Vigilante Task Force?

443
00:26:13,167 --> 00:26:16,708
To interdict, apprehend,
and prosecute extra-legal vigilantes

444
00:26:16,792 --> 00:26:18,458
to the fullest extent of the law.

445
00:26:18,542 --> 00:26:20,125
"To the fullest extent of the law"?

446
00:26:20,208 --> 00:26:21,708
That sounds serious.

447
00:26:22,292 --> 00:26:23,375
As a heart attack.

448
00:26:24,542 --> 00:26:25,750
[Matt] Huh.

449
00:26:25,833 --> 00:26:28,667
And, Officer Powell,
who formed the Task Force, and...

450
00:26:29,417 --> 00:26:31,875
created these, uh, parameters?

451
00:26:33,292 --> 00:26:34,292
Mayor Fisk.

452
00:26:36,292 --> 00:26:37,292
Of course.

453
00:26:37,375 --> 00:26:39,583
[Kirsten] Can you tell me about
those scars on your face?

454
00:26:40,083 --> 00:26:43,500
I got these in a firefight
with Daredevil and Frank Castle.

455
00:26:43,583 --> 00:26:45,792
-In Mr. Murdock's apartment?
-Yes.

456
00:26:47,583 --> 00:26:48,958
[Kirsten] Why were you there?

457
00:26:49,042 --> 00:26:52,833
Um, we were performing a welfare check.

458
00:26:54,292 --> 00:26:55,458
Welfare check?

459
00:26:57,458 --> 00:27:00,250
With assault rifles
and MRAP personnel carriers?

460
00:27:00,958 --> 00:27:03,708
I don't know, seems like
a lot of hardware for a blind lawyer.

461
00:27:03,792 --> 00:27:05,458
[audience chuckles]

462
00:27:08,083 --> 00:27:09,375
Was the defendant there?

463
00:27:12,375 --> 00:27:14,458
I was told she drove the getaway vehicle.

464
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:17,417
You were told?

465
00:27:18,125 --> 00:27:20,250
What else did Officer Powell
tell you to do?

466
00:27:21,458 --> 00:27:23,167
Did he tell you to kill Hector Ayala?

467
00:27:23,833 --> 00:27:25,708
-Or maybe that was Mayor Fisk.
-Objection.

468
00:27:25,792 --> 00:27:28,083
Immaterial, misleading, and prejudicial.

469
00:27:28,167 --> 00:27:30,000
Sustained. Ms. McDuffie,

470
00:27:30,083 --> 00:27:32,167
I will caution you against these theatrics

471
00:27:32,250 --> 00:27:34,667
and remind you that
there's no jury to play to here.

472
00:27:34,750 --> 00:27:36,208
Sure about that, Your Honor?

473
00:27:39,750 --> 00:27:40,750
No further questions.

474
00:27:40,833 --> 00:27:41,833
Thank you.

475
00:27:49,917 --> 00:27:52,625
-[line rings]
-[woman on phone] Alan Steverud's office.

476
00:27:52,708 --> 00:27:53,750
It's me.

477
00:27:54,000 --> 00:27:55,292
I need the Attorney General.

478
00:27:56,625 --> 00:27:58,000
-[AG Steverud] Steverud.
-Alan,

479
00:27:58,375 --> 00:28:01,167
I think it's time we move forward
on the suspension paperwork.

480
00:28:01,667 --> 00:28:04,750
Fisk's reign is over.
But we do need to move quick, though.

481
00:28:06,083 --> 00:28:08,250
No, it's-- It's gotten outta hand. It's...

482
00:28:09,292 --> 00:28:11,125
Yeah-- Our window is now.

483
00:28:13,042 --> 00:28:14,042
Okay.

484
00:28:35,042 --> 00:28:36,042
Daniel?

485
00:28:37,292 --> 00:28:38,292
What's going on?

486
00:28:40,375 --> 00:28:41,375
Daniel!

487
00:28:43,208 --> 00:28:45,708
You know, it's not just Fisk and Buck.

488
00:28:46,542 --> 00:28:47,542
It's me, too.

489
00:28:48,458 --> 00:28:49,583
I've done things.

490
00:28:50,125 --> 00:28:52,500
Really, really fucked up things.

491
00:28:54,000 --> 00:28:55,375
What're you talking about?

492
00:28:57,625 --> 00:28:59,167
I went upstate with Buck,

493
00:29:00,500 --> 00:29:02,583
to the Catskills, and we buried a body.

494
00:29:04,208 --> 00:29:05,208
Jesus.

495
00:29:09,208 --> 00:29:11,167
And I wish I didn't know I did that.

496
00:29:16,875 --> 00:29:17,875
But I can't...

497
00:29:18,708 --> 00:29:20,833
have anyone else knowing I did that.

498
00:29:41,167 --> 00:29:42,167
Come on.

499
00:29:50,000 --> 00:29:51,583
This isn't a safe house, is it?

500
00:29:52,167 --> 00:29:53,667
Daniel. Daniel!

501
00:29:53,750 --> 00:29:55,125
Daniel, please! Daniel!

502
00:29:56,667 --> 00:30:00,500
Is this really the person you wanna be?
[breathing heavily]

503
00:30:10,000 --> 00:30:11,208
Fuck! Fuck.

504
00:30:11,292 --> 00:30:13,625
Come on. Come on, before he sees.

505
00:30:17,625 --> 00:30:19,083
Here, take this

506
00:30:19,583 --> 00:30:22,250
and go. Don't go home.
Don't tell me where.

507
00:30:22,333 --> 00:30:24,417
And do not go anyplace
he would look, okay?

508
00:30:25,167 --> 00:30:27,875
-What're you gonna do?
-Doing the right thing. Just let me.

509
00:30:30,917 --> 00:30:31,917
Thank you.

510
00:30:32,917 --> 00:30:34,083
Of course.

511
00:30:36,542 --> 00:30:37,708
Just make it count.

512
00:30:48,125 --> 00:30:50,667
[Chief Justice Waters] This court
is adjourned until tomorrow morning.

513
00:30:54,625 --> 00:30:55,875
-Yeah.
-Thank you.

514
00:30:57,583 --> 00:30:59,333
I've got it. You focus on the rest.

515
00:31:00,750 --> 00:31:03,375
-That went as well as I thought.
-Yeah, I know. It's okay.

516
00:31:03,458 --> 00:31:04,458
It's okay.

517
00:31:05,208 --> 00:31:06,208
Be careful.

518
00:31:06,292 --> 00:31:07,292
[Matt] You, too.

519
00:31:12,792 --> 00:31:14,167
They're not leaving, are they?

520
00:31:16,125 --> 00:31:17,292
No, they're not.

521
00:31:18,500 --> 00:31:20,000
